    "As the work of Fouladvand et al. (2021) only demonstrated this approach using two data streams, we cannot attest its adequacy when more streams are used.",
    "The second requirement is associated with the use of continuous data since transformers are based on discrete vocabularies (R2).",
    "Two main approaches can be used in this situation:",
    "• At the vocabulary level (R2a): This case relies on categorizing continuous values to create a vocabulary for each of their types.",
    "As discussed by Siebra et al. (2022), while this process is simple, it presents the loss of granularity as a drawback."
